## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates **password security auditing techniques** in a **controlled cybersecurity lab environment** using **John the Ripper**, one of the most widely used password‑cracking tools.

The goal of this project is to **analyze password strength and highlight common weaknesses** in authentication systems through **hash extraction and dictionary-based attacks**. The lab provides a practical understanding of how attackers may attempt to crack weak passwords and how organizations can improve their password security policies.

⚠️ **Important:**  
All demonstrations are conducted in a **safe lab environment for educational and ethical cybersecurity learning purposes only**.

